{{ThisDateInRecentYears}}
{{Day}}

The [[Northern Hemisphere]] is considered to be halfway through its [[summer]] and the [[Southern Hemisphere]] half way through its [[winter]] on this day.

==Events==
*[[322 BC]] &amp;ndash; [[Battle of Crannon]] between [[Athens]] and Macedon.
* [[626]] &amp;ndash; The [[Eurasian Avar|Avar]] and [[Slavs|Slav]] armies leave the [[siege of Constantinople (626)|siege of Constantinople]].
* [[936]] &amp;ndash; Coronation of King [[Otto I of Germany]].
*[[1420]] &amp;ndash; Construction of the dome of [[Santa Maria del Fiore]] begins in [[Florence]].
*[[1427]] &amp;ndash; The [[House of Visconti|Visconti]] of Milan's fleet is destroyed by the [[Republic of Venice|Venetians]] on the [[Po River]].
*[[1461]] &amp;ndash; The [[Ming Dynasty]] [[China|Chinese]] military general Cao Qin [[Rebellion of Cao Qin|stages a coup]] against the [[Zhengtong Emperor|Tianshun Emperor]].
*[[1679]] &amp;ndash; The [[brigantine]] ''[[Le Griffon]]'', commissioned by [[René Robert Cavelier, Sieur de La Salle]], is towed to the south-eastern end of the [[Niagara River]], to become the first ship to sail the upper [[Great Lakes]] of [[North America]].
*[[1714]] &amp;ndash; The [[Battle of Gangut]]: the first important victory of the [[Russian Navy]].
*[[1782]] &amp;ndash; [[George Washington]] orders the creation of the [[Badge of Military Merit]] to honor soldiers wounded in battle. It is later renamed to the more poetic [[Purple Heart]].
*[[1789]] &amp;ndash; The [[United States War Department]] is established.
*[[1791]] &amp;ndash; United States troops destroy the [[Miami tribe|Miami]] town of [[Battle of Kenapacomaqua|Kenapacomaqua]] near the site of present-day [[Logansport, Indiana]] in the [[Northwest Indian War]].
*[[1794]] &amp;ndash; U.S. President [[George Washington]] invokes the [[Militia Law of 1792]] to suppress the [[Whiskey Rebellion]] in [[western Pennsylvania]].
*[[1819]] &amp;ndash; [[Simón Bolívar]] triumphs over [[Spain]] in the [[Battle of Boyacá]].
*[[1879]] &amp;ndash; The opening of the [[Poor Man's Palace]] in [[Manchester]].
*[[1890]] &amp;ndash; [[Anna Månsdotter]] becomes the last woman in [[Sweden]] to be executed, for the 1889 [[Yngsjö murder]].
*[[1927]] &amp;ndash; The [[Peace Bridge]] opens between [[Fort Erie, Ontario|Fort Erie]], [[Ontario]] and [[Buffalo, New York|Buffalo]], [[New York]].
*[[1930]] &amp;ndash; The last [[lynching]] in the Northern United States occurs in [[Marion, Indiana]]. Two men, [[Thomas Shipp and Abram Smith]], are killed.
*[[1933]] &amp;ndash; The [[Simele massacre]]: The [[Iraqi Government]] [[Simele massacre|slaughters]] over 3,000 [[Assyrian people|Assyrians]] in the village of [[Sumail]]. The day becomes known as Assyrian Martyrs Day.
*[[1940]] &amp;ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Alsace Lorraine]] is annexed by the Third Reich.
*[[1942]] &amp;ndash; World War II: the [[Battle of Guadalcanal]] begins &amp;ndash; [[United States Marine Corps|United States Marines]] initiate the first [[United States|American]] offensive of the war with landings on [[Guadalcanal (Pacific Ocean island)|Guadalcanal]] and [[Battle of Tulagi and Gavutu-Tanambogo|Tulagi]] in the [[Solomon Islands]].
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; [[IBM]] dedicates the first program-controlled [[calculator]], the [[Automatic Sequence Controlled Calculator]] (known best as the [[Harvard Mark I]]).
*[[1947]] &amp;ndash; [[Thor Heyerdahl]]'s [[balsa wood]] raft the [[Kon-Tiki]], smashes into the [[reef]] at [[Raroia]] in the [[Tuamotu Islands]] after a 101-day, {{Convert|7000|km|mi}} journey across the [[Pacific Ocean]] in an attempt to prove that pre-historic peoples could have traveled from [[South America]].
*  1947   &amp;ndash; The [[Bombay Municipal Corporation]] formally takes over the [[Bombay Electric Supply and Transport]] (BEST).
*[[1955]] &amp;ndash; [[Tokyo Telecommunications Engineering]], the precursor to [[Sony]], sells its first [[transistor radio]]s in [[Japan]].
*[[1959]] &amp;ndash; The [[Lincoln Memorial]] design on the U.S. [[Cent (United States coin)|penny]] goes into circulation. It replaces the &quot;sheaves of wheat&quot; design and is still in use.
*  1959   &amp;ndash; [[Explorer program]]: [[Explorer 6]] launches from the [[Atlantic Missile Range]] in [[Cape Canaveral, Florida|Cape Canaveral]], [[Florida]].
*[[1960]] &amp;ndash; [[Côte d'Ivoire]] becomes independent.
*[[1964]] &amp;ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: the [[Congress of the United States|U.S. Congress]] passes the [[Gulf of Tonkin Resolution]] giving [[President of the United States|US President]] [[Lyndon B. Johnson]] broad war powers to deal with [[North Vietnam]]ese attacks on [[United States|American]] forces.
*[[1964]] &amp;ndash; [[Prometheus (tree)|Prometheus]], a [[bristlecone pine]] and the world's oldest [[tree]], is cut down.
*[[1965]] &amp;ndash; The infamous first party between [[Ken Kesey]]'s [[Merry Pranksters]] and motorcycle gang the [[Hells Angels]] takes place at Kesey's estate in [[La Honda]], [[California]] introducing psychedelics to the gang world and forever linking the [[hippie]] movement to the Hell's Angels.
*[[1966]] &amp;ndash; [[Race riot]]s occur in [[Lansing, Michigan|Lansing]], [[Michigan]].
*[[1967]] &amp;ndash; Vietnam War: the [[People's Republic of China]] agrees to give [[North Vietnam]] an undisclosed amount of aid in the form of a grant.
*[[1970]] &amp;ndash; California judge [[Harold Haley]] is taken hostage in his courtroom and killed during in an effort to free [[George Jackson (Black Panther)|George Jackson]] from police custody.
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; [[Philippe Petit]] performs a high wire act between the twin towers of the [[World Trade Center]] {{Convert|1368|ft|m}} in the air.
*[[1976]] &amp;ndash; [[Viking program]]: [[Viking 2]] enters orbit around [[Mars]].
*[[1978]] &amp;ndash; [[President of the United States|U.S. President]] [[Jimmy Carter]] declares a federal emergency at [[Love Canal]].
*[[1979]] &amp;ndash; [[1979 Woodstock, Ontario tornado|Several tornadoes]] struck the city of Woodstock, Ontario, Canada and the surrounding communities.
*[[1981]] &amp;ndash; ''[[The Washington Star]]'' ceases all operations after 128 years of publication.
*[[1985]] &amp;ndash; [[Takao Doi]], [[Mamoru Mohri]] and [[Chiaki Mukai]] are chosen to be [[Japan|Japan's]] first [[astronaut]]s.
*[[1988]] &amp;ndash; [[Tompkins Square Park Police Riot (1988)|Rioting]] in [[New York City]]'s [[Tompkins Square Park]].
*[[1989]] &amp;ndash; [[U.S. Congress]]man [[Mickey Leland]] (D-[[Texas|TX]]) and 15 others die in a [[plane crash]] in [[Ethiopia]].
*[[1998]] &amp;ndash; [[1998 United States embassy bombings|The United States embassy bombings]] in [[Dar es Salaam]], [[Tanzania]] and [[Nairobi]], [[Kenya]] kill approximately 212 people.
*[[1999]] &amp;ndash; [[Second Chechen War]] began.
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; [[Barry Bonds]] of the [[San Francisco Giants]] breaks [[baseball]] great [[Hank Aaron]]'s record by hitting his 756th [[home run]].
*[[2008]] &amp;ndash; [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] launches a military offensive against [[South Ossetia]] to counter the alleged [[Russia]]n invasion, starting the [[2008 South Ossetia War|South Ossetia War]].

