      <text xml:space="preserve">{{pp-move-indef}}{{AugustCalendar|float=right}}
{{ThisDateInRecentYears}}
{{Day}}

==Events==
*[[1220]] &amp;ndash; [[Sweden]] is defeated by [[Estonians|Estonian]] tribes in the [[Battle of Lihula]].
*[[1503]] &amp;ndash; King [[James IV of Scotland]] marries [[Margaret Tudor]], daughter of King [[Henry VII of England]] at [[Holyrood Abbey]], [[Edinburgh]], [[Scotland]].
*[[1509]] &amp;ndash; The Emperor [[Krishnadevaraya|Krishnadeva Raya]] is crowned, marking the beginning of the regeneration of the [[Vijayanagara Empire]].
*[[1576]] &amp;ndash; The cornerstone for [[Tycho Brahe]]'s [[Uraniborg]] observatory is laid on [[Hven]].
*[[1585]] &amp;ndash; [[John Davis (English explorer)|John Davis]] enters [[Cumberland Sound]] in search of the [[Northwest Passage]].
*[[1588]] &amp;ndash; [[Anglo-Spanish War (1585)|Anglo-Spanish War]]: [[Spanish Armada#Battle of Gravelines|Battle of Gravelines]] &amp;ndash; The naval engagement ends, ending the [[Spanish Armada]]'s attempt to invade England.
*[[1605]] &amp;ndash; The city of [[Oulu]], [[Finland]], is founded by [[Charles IX of Sweden]].
*[[1647]] &amp;ndash; The [[Irish Confederate Wars]] and [[Wars of the Three Kingdoms]]: [[Battle of Dungans Hill]] &amp;ndash; [[England|English]] [[Parliament]]ary forces defeat [[Ireland|Irish]] forces.
*[[1709]] &amp;ndash; [[Bartolomeu de Gusmão]] demonstrates the lifting power of hot air in an audience before the King of Portugal in [[Lisbon]]
*[[1786]] &amp;ndash; [[Mont Blanc]] on the [[France|French]] – [[Italy|Italian]] border is climbed for the first time by [[Jacques Balmat]] and Dr [[Michel-Gabriel Paccard]].
*[[1793]] &amp;ndash; The [[insurrection of Lyon]] occurs during the French Revolution.
*[[1794]] &amp;ndash; [[Joseph Whidbey]] leads an expedition to search for the [[Northwest Passage]] near [[Juneau, Alaska]].
*[[1839]] &amp;ndash; [[Beta Theta Pi]] is founded in [[Oxford, Ohio]].
*[[1844]] &amp;ndash; The [[Quorum of the Twelve Apostles]], headed by [[Brigham Young]], is reaffirmed as the leading body of [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]] (LDS Church).
*[[1863]] &amp;ndash; [[American Civil War]]: following his defeat in the [[Battle of Gettysburg]], General [[Robert E. Lee]] sends a letter of resignation to [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] President [[Jefferson Davis]] (which is refused upon receipt).
*[[1870]] &amp;ndash; The ''[[Republic of Ploieşti]]'', a failed [[Liberalism in Romania|Radical-Liberal]] rising against [[Domnitor]] [[Carol I of Romania|Carol]] of [[Romania]].
*[[1876]] &amp;ndash; [[Thomas Edison]] receives a patent for his [[mimeograph]].
*[[1908]] &amp;ndash; [[Wilbur Wright]] makes his first flight at a racecourse at [[Le Mans]], France. It is the Wright Brothers' first public flight.
*[[1910]] &amp;ndash; The US Army installs the first tricycle landing gear on the Army's [[Wright Flyer]].
*[[1911]] &amp;ndash; The millionth patent is filed in the [[United States Patent Office]] by Francis Holton for a tubeless vehicle tire.
*  1911   &amp;ndash; [[Public Law 62-5]] sets the number of representatives in the [[United States House of Representatives]] at 435. The law would come into effect in [[1913]].
*[[1918]] &amp;ndash; [[World War I]]: the [[Battle of Amiens (1918)|Battle of Amiens]] begins a string of almost continuous victories with a push through the [[Germany|German]] front lines ([[Hundred Days Offensive]]).
*[[1929]] &amp;ndash; The [[Germany|German]] airship ''[[LZ 127 Graf Zeppelin|Graf Zeppelin]]'' begins a round-the-world flight.
*[[1931]] &amp;ndash; Workers go on strike at the [[Hoover dam]].
*[[1938]] &amp;ndash; The building of [[Mauthausen concentration camp]] begins.
*[[1940]] &amp;ndash; The &quot;[[Aufbau Ost (1940)|Aufbau Ost]]&quot; directive is signed by [[Wilhelm Keitel]].
*[[1942]] &amp;ndash; [[World War II]]: in [[Washington, DC]], six [[Germany|German]] would-be saboteurs ([[Operation Pastorius]]) are executed.
*  1942   &amp;ndash; The [[Quit India]] resolution is passed by the [[Bombay]] session of the [[All India Congress Committee]] in [[Mumbai|Bombay]], and [[Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi|Mahatma Gandhi]] gave the &quot;[[Quit India speech]]&quot; at [[Gowalia Tank]], leading to the start of a civil disobedience movement across [[British India]].
*[[1945]] &amp;ndash; World War II: the [[Soviet Union]] declares war on [[Japan]] and begins the [[Manchurian Strategic Offensive Operation]].
*  1945   &amp;ndash; The [[United Nations Charter]] is signed by the [[United States]], which becomes the third nation to join.
*[[1946]] &amp;ndash; First flight of the [[Convair B-36]].
*[[1949]] &amp;ndash; [[Bhutan]] becomes independent.
*[[1960]] &amp;ndash; [[South Kasai]] secedes from the [[Republic of the Congo (Léopoldville)|Congo]].
*[[1963]] &amp;ndash; [[The Great Train Robbery of 1963|Great Train Robbery]]: in England, a gang of 15 [[train robbery|train robbers]] steal 2.6 million pounds in bank notes.
*[[1967]] &amp;ndash; The [[Association of Southeast Asian Nations]] (ASEAN) is founded by [[Indonesia]], [[Malaysia]], the [[Philippines]], [[Singapore]] and [[Thailand]].
*[[1968]] &amp;ndash; Jurō Wada successfully performs [[Japan|Japan's]] first [[Organ transplant|heart transplant]].
*[[1973]] &amp;ndash; U.S. Vice President [[Spiro Agnew]] appears on television to denounce accusations he had taken [[kickbacks]] while governor of [[Maryland]].
*  1973   &amp;ndash; [[Kim Dae-Jung]], a [[South Korea]]n politician and later president of South Korea, is [[Kidnapping of Kim Dae-jung|kidnapped]].
*[[1974]] &amp;ndash; [[Watergate scandal]]: U.S. President [[Richard Nixon]] announces his resignation, effective the next day.
*[[1976]] &amp;ndash; As part of the [[American Basketball Association|ABA]]-[[National Basketball Association|NBA]] [[ABA–NBA merger|merger agreement]], a [[ABA-NBA merger#ABA Dispersal Draft, 1976|dispersal draft]] is conducted to assign teams for the players on the two ABA franchises which had folded.
*[[1980]] &amp;ndash; The [[Central Hotel Fire, Bundoran]] occurs in Ireland.
*[[1988]] &amp;ndash; The &quot;[[8888 Uprising]]&quot; occurs in [[Burma]].
*  1988   &amp;ndash; The lights are turned on at [[Wrigley Field]] for the first time, making it the last major league stadium to host night games. (The game, against the [[Philadelphia Phillies]], is rained out after three-and-a-half innings.)
*[[1989]] &amp;ndash; [[Space Shuttle program]]: [[STS-28]] Mission &amp;ndash; [[Space Shuttle Columbia]] takes off on a secret five-day military mission.
*[[1990]] &amp;ndash; [[Iraq]] occupies [[Kuwait]] and the state is annexed to Iraq. This would lead to the [[Gulf War]] shortly afterward.
*[[1991]] &amp;ndash; The [[Warsaw radio mast]], at one time the tallest construction ever built, collapses.
*[[2000]] &amp;ndash; [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] submarine ''[[H.L. Hunley]]'' is raised to the surface after 136 years on the ocean floor and 30 years after its discovery by undersea explorer [[E. Lee Spence]] and 5 years after being filmed by a dive team funded by novelist [[Clive Cussler]].
*[[2007]] &amp;ndash; An EF2 [[tornado]] touches down in [[Kings County, New York|Kings County]] and [[Richmond County, New York|Richmond County]], [[New York State]], the most powerful tornado in New York to date and the first in Brooklyn since 1889.
*[[2009]] &amp;ndash; [[Typhoon Morakot]] makes landfall in Taiwan, and almost the entire southern region of Taiwan is flooded by record-breaking rainfall.
&lt;!-- DO NOT ADD 2008 OLYMPICS TO THIS LIST. It is a regularly recurring event and thus not noteworthy. --&gt;

